Cell.Text: Know of an old guy hiding out in Riften, name of Esbern?
[S] Lot of people looking for him. Don't know his name, but he's paid good money for nobody to know he's down here.
I'm looking for an old guy hiding out in Riften, probably in the Ratway.
[S] Well... there is guy like that. He's paid good money for nobody to know he's down here, but I guess I can tell you.
That old guy hiding out down here... where did he live?
[S] He's holed up in the Ratway Warrens. Be careful. You're not the only one looking for him.
I'm looking for an old guy, hiding out somewhere in Riften.
[S] Huh. Lot of old guys around. I don't really know how I can help.
Know of an old guy hiding out in Riften, name of Esbern?

[S] Don't know his name, but there is an guy like that hiding out down here. Paid plenty for nobody to know about it. | You're not the first person to come in here asking about him, either, so be careful.
I'm looking for an old guy hiding out in Riften, probably in the Ratway.
[S] Yeah, I think I know who you mean. He's paid good money for nobody to know he's down here, but I guess I can tell you.
That old guy hiding out down here... where did he live?
[S] Down in the Ratway Warrens. Nice place, if you don't mind the stench, rats, and assorted lowlifes as neighbors.
[S] That's interesting. Why do I care? You want a drink, or maybe just a few broken bones?

[S] Never heard of anybody like that. But if you want to hide out in Riften, the Ratway's where you'd be. | There's a sort of tavern down there, the Ragged Flagon. Where all the lowlifes in Riften get drunk and knife each other. | You might try there, if you can get through the Ratway alive.

Node.Caption: MQ202RatwayEsbernTopic: I'm looking for an old guy, hiding out somewhere in Riften.

Cell.Text: [S] <<Shared>> He's holed up in the Ratway Warrens. Hardly ever leaves the place - has someone bring him food and such. | Crazy old coot, from what I've heard. For that to stand out down here, he must really be off his nut.
[S] <<Shared>> He lives somewhere in the Ratway Warrens. Must be crazy or desperate to live down there. Maybe both.
Dangerous-looking elves who didn't give their names. Draw your own conclusions.
Various shady types I've never seen before. I'd watch my back if I was you.

Node.Caption: MQ202WhosHuntingForEsbernTopic: Who else is looking for Esbern?

Cell.Text: [S] Yeah. I bet I know your guy. He's hiding out in the Ratway Warrens. Paying us good coin for nobody to know about it.

Node.Caption: MQ202ByrnjolfEsbernTopic: I'm looking for an old guy, probably hiding out in the Ratway.

Cell.Text: [S] What?! No, that's not me. I'm not Esbern. I don't know what you're talking about.

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernThroughDoorA1: Esbern? Open the door. I'm a friend.

Cell.Text: S|Go away!
[S] I told you to go away. I'm not opening this door for anybody!
Delphine? How do you... so you've finally found her, and she led you to me. And here I am, caught like a rat in a trap.
[S] Oh, how reassuring! Most likely you're with the Thalmor and this is just a trick to get me to open the door!

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernThroughDoorB2: The Thalmor have found you. You need to get out of here.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Ah. Indeed, indeed. I do remember. | Delphine really is alive, then? You'd better come in then and tell me how you found me and what you want.

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernThroughDoorC3: Delphine said to "remember the 30th of Frostfall".

Cell.Text: [S] G|What's that you said? Dragonborn? Then... there really is hope after all? | You'd better come inside. Quickly now. Thalmor agents have been seen in the Ratway.

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernThroughDoorC2: I'm the one the Blades have been searching for. I'm Dragonborn.

Cell.Text: [S] G|And no doubt you're one of them. Leave me alone!

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernThroughDoorC1: There are Thalmor agents in the Ratway. Looking for you.

Cell.Text: G|Pff. Go away, if you know what's good for you.
G|I got nothing to say to you.
G|I'm not looking for a conversation.
G|Leave me alone.
[S] Maybe I'm just getting soft in my old age, but I actually believe you.
That's a touching story. Now get outta my face.
[S] A friend, huh? Well... then it's probably okay if I tell you.
I guess you don't hear too well. I never heard of this "friend" of yours.

Node.Caption: MQ202RatwayEsbernPersuade: I need to talk to him. I'm a friend. His life's in danger. (Persuade)

Cell.Text: [S] Well... when you put it that way, I think I do know the old guy you're talking about.
Big talk for someone with a light purse.
[S] You know what? I think I do know the guy you're talking about.
Maybe it would. If you had it.

Node.Caption: MQ202RatwayEsbernBribe: Maybe this will help your memory. ( Gold)

Cell.Text: [S] There's no need for that. Not like he's a friend of mine or anything. Just calm down.
Are you going to tell me, or am I going to have to beat it out of you? (Brawl)
[S] G|You've got a lot of nerve. But not a lot of common sense.
I can break some of your bones if that's what it's going to take...
[S] Easy there. I don't want that kind of trouble. Guy ain't worth it.
I can break some of your bones if that's what it's going to take... (Brawl)
[S] G|Yeah. That's what it's going to take.

Node.Caption: MQ202RatwayEsbernIntimidate: Are you going to tell me, or am I going to have to beat it out of you?

Cell.Text: [S] G|She does? She's come to see the truth, at long last? | You'd better come in and tell me how you found me and what you want.
G|Delphine needs my help? You don't know Delphine very well if you think I would believe that. Now go away!

Node.Caption: MQ202EsbernThroughDoorC4: Delphine needs your help to stop the dragons. (Persuade)
